### BUG-7: `SharedLink.expiresAt` is declared NOT NULL in SQL but nullable in Java
**File**: [`SharedLink.java`](file:///c:/Users/Anmol%20Raj/OneDrive/Desktop/Java%20Project/src/main/java/com/cloudnest/entity/SharedLink.java#L52)

**Exact Issue**:
```java
// In SharedLink.java:
@Column(name = "expires_at")  // nullable in Java!
private LocalDateTime expiresAt;

// Comment says "null = never expires"
public boolean isExpired() {
    return expiresAt != null && LocalDateTime.now().isAfter(expiresAt);
}
```
But in `schema.sql`:
```sql
expires_at  TIMESTAMP NOT NULL   -- Line 56
```
The SQL schema enforces `NOT NULL`, but the Java entity allows null. Hibernate's `ddl-auto=update` will NOT make it nullable. If you try to create a `SharedLink` without `expiresAt`, you get a **`DataIntegrityViolationException`**. Since `SharedLinkService.generateShareLink()` always sets `expiresAt`, it works now — but if someone adds a "no expiry" feature in the future, it will fail silently.

**Fix**: Align them. Either:
- Remove `NOT NULL` from schema (to allow non-expiring links), **or**
- Add `@Column(name = "expires_at", nullable = false)` to the entity

