### BUG-9: `FileStorageService` has a SHA-256 hash computed on **already-written** file — TOCTOU window
**File**: [`FileStorageService.java`](file:///c:/Users/Anmol%20Raj/OneDrive/Desktop/Java%20Project/src/main/java/com/cloudnest/service/FileStorageService.java#L98-L140)

**Exact Issue (Race Condition)**:
```java
// Step 1: Copy file to disk
Files.copy(file.getInputStream(), targetPath, ...);

// Step 2: Compute hash from the ALREADY-WRITTEN file (reads it back from disk!)
try (InputStream is = Files.newInputStream(targetPath)) {
    // ... SHA-256 computation ...
}

// Step 3: If duplicate found, delete the file we just wrote
if (existingFile != null) {
    Files.deleteIfExists(targetPath);
}
```
This approach:
1. **Wastes disk I/O**: Writes the file first, then reads it back to hash it. Should hash from `file.getInputStream()` directly.
2. **Opens a TOCTOU window**: Under concurrent uploads of the same file, two threads may both write the file before either checks for a duplicate.

**Fix**: Compute hash directly from `MultipartFile.getInputStream()` before writing to disk:
```java
// Hash first, then check deduplication, then write (or skip write)
String fileHash = computeSha256(file.getInputStream());
FileEntity existingFile = fileRepository.findFirstByFileHash(fileHash);
if (existingFile != null) {
    storedName = existingFile.getStoredName();
    node = existingFile.getStorageNode();
} else {
    // Only now write the file to disk
    Files.copy(file.getInputStream(), targetPath, ...);
}
```
Note: `MultipartFile.getInputStream()` can only be read once; use `file.getBytes()` or buffer it.

