### Missing Dependency: `@Modifying` without `@Query` on `SharedLinkRepository`
**File**: [`SharedLinkRepository.java`](file:///c:/Users/Anmol%20Raj/OneDrive/Desktop/Java%20Project/src/main/java/com/cloudnest/repository/SharedLinkRepository.java#L30-L31)
```java
@org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.Modifying
void deleteByFileId(Long fileId);
```
`@Modifying` should always be paired with `@Transactional` at the repository method level (or the calling service must be `@Transactional`). The callers (`SharedLinkService.deleteLinksForFile()`) **does not call this method at all** — `deleteLinksForFile()` is never called when files are deleted! This means **shared links are orphaned in the database when files are permanently deleted** (though the FK CASCADE handles DB integrity, the links exist as dangling records before hard-delete).

> [!WARNING]
> `SharedLinkService.deleteLinksForFile()` is defined but **never called** by `FileStorageService.permanentDeleteFile()` or `FolderService.permanentDeleteFolder()`. Shared link records are only cleaned up by the FK `ON DELETE CASCADE` in PostgreSQL (schema.sql line 54), not from application code.

